# Original Idea

Add ability to voice control creating herdr sessions and initializing new agents and kicking them off etc. should support claude code, codex, grok, `cursor-agent`, and other coding clis (must be able to be done ad-hoc). For the supported ones, we should see if we have aliases for them: cc for claude, cx for codex, gk for grok. cr for cursor-agent. If we have the 2 letter alias present, we should use that, otherwise we should use the normal cli command to start a session.

